GlobalVariables.StudyDescription: This file contains the metadata, events, and data for REDCap project "eLwazi Catalogue MetaData Management Project".
GlobalVariables.redcap:ProjectNotes: This project is intended to provide DS-I Africa Research Hubs with the access to manage and submit there own metadata and progress status on their datasets they are working on that will end up in the eLwazi catalogue

Question.TranslatedText: Please be aware that by selecting 'I agree' you are consenting to your information being shared with the eLwazi team for ongoing communications, tracking, evaluation and reporting purposes. Your personal information will be de-identified whenever used in any type of reporting. Furthermore, your personal information will not be shared with any 3rd parties beyond eLwazi without your explicit permission. You may also at any time request that your information be removed from this database. To remove your information please contact https://helpdesk.elwazi.org/. The project metadata that you share on this database will be used specifically for public display on the eLwazi Catalogue, the metadata can be updated, edited and maintained by yourself as the project Data Steward. If you have queries you can also communicate directly with the eLwazi Data Support Working Group leads: Lyndon Zass or Tony Burdett.
Question.redcap:FormattedTranslatedText:
Please be aware that by selecting 'I agree' you are consenting to your information being shared with the eLwazi team for ongoing communications, tracking, evaluation and reporting purposes. Your personal information will be de-identified whenever used in any type of reporting. Furthermore, your personal information will not be shared with any 3rd parties beyond eLwazi without your explicit permission. You may also at any time request that your information be removed from this database. To remove your information please contact https://helpdesk.elwazi.org/. 

The project metadata that you share on this database will be used specifically for public display on the eLwazi Catalogue, the metadata can be updated, edited and maintained by yourself as the project Data Steward. If you have queries you can also communicate directly with the eLwazi Data Support Working Group leads: Lyndon Zass or Tony Burdett.
